Key Match Events: Lebanon and China PR settled for a 0-0 draw in their AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023 Group A match at the Al Thumama Stadium.
Lebanon's Khalil Khamsi saw his header from Kassem El Zein’s throw-in collected safely by goalkeeper Yan Junling.
Wu Lei took advantage of a loose ball from defender Nour Mansoor to set up Lui Bin Bin, but the latter’s effort was punched away by Lebanese custodian Mostafa Matar.
Omar Chaban's right-footed attempt hit the side netting.
Dai Weijun forced Matar into action, with the custodian needing two attempts to deny the China number 9.
Hasan Matouk’s right-footed shot from outside the box was denied by the crossbar.
Zhang Linpeng’s header from the centre of the box had to be parried away.
Hasan Srour’s right-footed shot from outside the box was fisted away by Junling.
Junling had to ward off a dangerous header from defender Maher Sabra.
Srour denied Wu Lei’s shot from inside the six-yard box.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The result took China PR to two points while it was Lebanon’s first point in the tournament.
Both teams have much to do on Matchday Three if they are to advance to the Round of 16.
China will face hosts Qatar on Monday while Lebanon will play against debutants Tajikistan.
